t? Sev is easier for you now too, cause you only need 4 friends (who can port right into the zone themselves too) to be available to come help instead of 30+.<br><br>Also, if you aren't in a big guild, the playing field just got more level for you too.  Instead of having to compete with a larger or better organized guild to race for Sev, you can now buy a green scale from the MB team at the same price as any warrior from one of those guilds you would have been racing.  That puts you on equal footing with warriors who would have had an advantage on you.<br><br>Buying the green scale does not cheapen your epic.  It is already a hard to obtain item.  If you are really ready for the warrior epic, Severilous is probably a reasonably easy fight, if not completely trivial.  So, you are not showing a lack of skill or worth by buying the scale... just avoiding a horrible camp.<br><br>So, go out and earn some xp and plat.  You will probably amass enough to buy the scale sooner than you could have successfully camped and killed Sev anyway, regardless of MB teams. <p><a href="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi/jedimaster.jpg" width="285" height="123" border="0"><br></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2"><b>Korak Sarathai - 59 Barbarian Myrmidon - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All in the reflexes</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1548<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 11: